/*
Step 1. Create App Registration for Databricks -> USed for Oauth from Spark -> ADLS
Step 2. Enter Application/ClientId and App Reg Secret Here in Parameters
Step 3. Upload Template
Step 4. Give App Registration Access to Blob -Storage Blob Data Contributor
Step 5. Give App Registration Access to Read/List Secrets in Access Policies of Key Vault
Step 5. Give AzureDatabricks Object Id access to KV and BlobStorage
Step 5. Create Secret Scope in Databricks https://<databricks-instance>#secrets/createScope //demoscope
          Example : https://adb-7361764398850383.3.azuredatabricks.net/?o=7361764398850383#secrets/createScope

Step 7. Need to setup account console for databricks - requires GA Role on Azure - Account or a GA to enable Account Admin
Step 8. Get into account consosle and set up Cloud Resource NCC and update the workspace with the NCC
Step 9. Configure Cluster with Secrets for Authentication
 
spark.hadoop.fs.azure.account.oauth.provider.type.btxprecisiondatalake.dfs.core.windows.net org.apache.hadoop.fs.azurebfs.oauth2.ClientCredsTokenProvider
spark.hadoop.fs.azure.account.auth.type.btxprecisiondatalake.dfs.core.windows.net OAuth
spark.hadoop.fs.azure.account.oauth2.client.id.btxprecisiondatalake.dfs.core.windows.net {{secrets/ScopeNameYouCreatedInStep5/app-client-id-secret}}
spark.hadoop.fs.azure.account.oauth2.client.endpoint.btxprecisiondatalake.dfs.core.windows.net {{secrets/ScopeNameYouCreatedInStep5/tenant-url}}
spark.hadoop.fs.azure.account.oauth2.client.secret.btxprecisiondatalake.dfs.core.windows.net {{secrets/ScopeNameYouCreatedInStep5/app-client-secret}}


aex.dev.azure.com to setup a brand new devops organization

*/







